South Africa Defeats West Indies by Seven Wickets at the Cricket World Cup

-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 
2011-02-24T16:17:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-24/south-africa-defeats-west-indies-by-seven-wickets-at-the-cricket-world-cup.html
  South Africa  defeated West Indies by
seven wickets in the opening game for both teams at the Cricket  World Cup .  AB de Villiers hit 107 as South Africa reached its victory
target of 223 in 42.5 overs in the Group B game in Delhi.
Captain Graeme Smith scored 45 and JP Duminy was 42 not out.  Imran Tahir took 4-41 as West Indies was bowled out for
222. Darren Bravo top-scored with 73.  The top four teams from each of the seven-team groups
advance to the quarterfinals after a round-robin competition.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  